description: Latin exsertus, past participle of exserere (“to stretch out or forth”). See exert.

adjectives.description: exsert (comparative more exsert, superlative most exsert)

entries.meaning: Standing out; projecting beyond some other part.

verbs.description: exsert (third-person singular simple present exserts, present participle exserting, simple past and past participle exserted)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To thrust out; to cause to protrude.
examples: Some worms are said to exsert the proboscis.
